Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
Diffindo Cakes and Bakes – E-Commerce Web Application

1	Introduction
1.1	Purpose
The purpose of this Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document is to describe the functional and non-functional requirements of the Diffindo Cakes and Bakes E-Commerce System.
This document provides a detailed description of the system features, system architecture, user interactions, and technical requirements needed for the development and operation of the application.
The document serves as a reference for developers, system administrators, testers, and project stakeholders.
1.2	Background
Diffindo Cakes and Bakes is an online bakery platform developed to provide customers with a convenient way to browse and order premium cakes and baked goods through the internet.
Traditional bakery ordering requires customers to physically visit the store. This system digitizes the ordering process and allows customers to place orders online easily.
The system also provides an administrative dashboard where administrators can manage products and process customer orders efficiently.\

1.3	Objectives
The main objectives of the system are:
•	Provide an online catalogue for bakery products
•	Allow customers to create accounts and place orders
•	Enable administrators to manage products and orders
•	Send order confirmation emails automatically
•	Provide a secure and user-friendly ordering system
1.4	Scope
The Diffindo Cakes and Bakes system is a web-based e-commerce application that enables customers to browse bakery products, add items to a shopping cart, and place orders online.
The system provides two main user roles:
Customer
•	Register and login
•	Browse products
•	Add items to cart
•	Checkout and place orders
•	View order history
Administrator
•	Manage products
•	Manage customer orders
•	Monitor store activity
The system is built using PHP, MySQL, HTML5, Tailwind CSS, and JavaScript.
2	Overall Description
2.1	Product Perspective
The Diffindo system is a standalone web application that connects customers with an online bakery store.
The system consists of three main layers:
User Browser
↓
Frontend Interface (HTML, Tailwind CSS, JavaScript)
↓
Backend Application (PHP)
↓
Database (MySQL)
2.2	Product Functions
The main functions of the system include:
Customer Functions:
•	User registration
•	User login/logout
•	Product browsing
•	Add products to cart
•	Remove products from cart
•	Checkout and place orders
•	Order history viewing
•	Email order confirmation
Admin Functions:
•	Admin login
•	Add new products
•	Edit product information
•	Delete products
•	View customer orders
•	Manage order details
2.3	User Classes and Characteristics
Customer
Customers are registered users who use the system to browse products and place orders.
Characteristics:
•	Basic internet knowledge
•	Uses web browser
•	Wants quick and easy ordering experience
Administrator
Administrators manage the system content and orders.
Characteristics:
•	Has full system access
•	Responsible for managing products and orders
•	Uses the admin dashboard
2.4	Operating Environment
The system operates in the following environment:
Component	Requirement
Web Browser	Chrome, Firefox, Edge
Server	Apache / Nginx
Backend	PHP 7.4 or higher
Database	MySQL 5.7 or higher
OS	Windows / Linux / Mac

2.5	Design Constraints
The system must follow the following constraints:
•	Developed using PHP and MySQL
•	Must run on standard web servers
•	Must support modern browsers
•	Must use responsive design
2.6	Assumptions and Dependencies
•	Users have internet access
•	SMTP email service is available
•	Database server is running
•	Administrator manages product inventory
3	Functional Requirements
3.1	User Registration
Users must be able to create an account by providing:
•	Name
•	Email address
•	Password
The system must validate the email and store the password securely.
3.2	User Authentication
Users must be able to login using their registered email and password.
The system must:
•	Verify credentials
•	Start a user session
•	Redirect the user to the homepage
3.3	Product Catalogue
Customers must be able to browse a list of available bakery products.
Each product should display:
•	Product image
•	Product name
•	Description
•	Price
3.4	Shopping Cart
Customers must be able to add products to a shopping cart.
Cart features include:
•	Add items
•	Remove items
•	View cart
•	Update quantity
3.5	Checkout and Order Processing
Customers must be able to place orders through the checkout process.
Process:
1.	User reviews cart
2.	User confirms order
3.	Order stored in database
4.	Email confirmation sent to customer
3.6	Order History
Customers must be able to view previous orders through their account.
3.7	Product Management (Admin)
Administrators must be able to:
•	Add new products
•	Edit product information
•	Delete products
•	Upload product images
3.8	Order Management (Admin)
Administrators must be able to:
•	View customer orders
•	Process and manage orders
•	Monitor order activity
4	Non-Functional Requirements
4.1	Security
The system must ensure:
•	Password encryption
•	Protection against SQL injection
•	Secure session management
•	Restricted admin access

4.2	Performance
The system should:
•	Respond within 3 seconds
•	Handle multiple users simultaneously
•	Optimize database queries

4.3	Usability
The system interface must be:
•	Easy to navigate
•	Responsive on mobile devices
•	Visually clean and simple

4.4	Reliability
The system must:
•	Store data securely
•	Maintain system stability
•	Support database backups
•	
4.5	Scalability
The system should support future enhancements such as:
•	Payment gateway integration
•	Mobile application support
•	Delivery tracking
5	System Design
5.1	System Architecture
The system uses a layered architecture consisting of:
Frontend Layer
•	HTML
•	Tailwind CSS
•	JavaScript
Backend Layer
•	PHP application logic
Database Layer
•	MySQL database
5.2	Database Entities
Main database tables include:
Table	Description
Users	Stores user accounts
Products	Stores bakery products
Orders	Stores order details
Order_Items	Stores items in each order
Cart	Temporary cart storage

6	Implementation
The system was implemented using modern web development technologies.
Technology Stack:
Backend: PHP 7.4+ with PDO
Database: MySQL
Frontend: HTML5, Tailwind CSS, JavaScript
Email Service: PHPMailer using Gmail SMTP
Development Tools:
•	Visual Studio Code
•	Laragon local server
•	phpMyAdmin
•	Git and GitHub
7	Software Quality and Testing
The system was tested using several testing methods.
Unit Testing
Testing individual modules such as login, cart, and product management.
Integration Testing
Testing communication between modules such as checkout and order processing.
System Testing
Testing the complete workflow of the application.
Acceptance Testing
Ensuring the system meets the project requirements.
Example Test Cases:
Test Case	Action	Expected Result
Login	Enter valid credentials	User successfully logs in
Add to Cart	Add product	Product appears in cart
Checkout	Place order	Order saved in database

8	Development Tools
The following tools were used during development:
Tool	Purpose
Git	Version control
GitHub	Project repository
Visual Studio Code	Code editor
Laragon	Local server
phpMyAdmin	Database management
Selenium	Automated testing
PHPMailer	Email notifications

9	Conclusion
The Diffindo Cakes and Bakes system successfully demonstrates the implementation of an online bakery ordering platform.
The system provides customers with a convenient way to browse products and place orders while allowing administrators to efficiently manage products and customer orders.
The project demonstrates the use of modern web technologies and software engineering practices in developing a functional e-commerce system.


